This paper is about analyzing deep neural networks using the Hessian matrix, which is a second-order derivative matrix. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves computations and analysis of large datasets, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, and cs.DS.
